<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112J72/1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Hartman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-05T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American citizens report imprisonment of R. B. Jones since December 17th
                            in an unjust and illegal manner. Upon inquiry from Department, Consul
                            General confirms this and states that strong measures are imperatively
                            needed. Also that Jones’ case has been fully and often reported to
                            Legation in accordance with Consular regulations. Report fully by
                            telegraph what action you have taken.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>